caller_intent: Bennett Jones from Johnson and Johnson Insurance wanted to schedule an in-person meeting with Rick but adjusted to a virtual meeting after learning Rick's Wednesday schedule was unavailable.
resolution_steps: Bennett proposed an in-person meeting on Wednesday, December 12th at 11 AM.
Rick explained his Wednesday schedule was fully booked with agency meetings.
Bennett offered alternative virtual meeting times: December 13th at 10 AM or December 11th at 4 PM.
Rick selected December 11th at 4 PM as the preferred virtual meeting time.
Bennett requested Rick's email address to send a calendar invite.
knowledge_required: Understanding of scheduling conflicts and alternative meeting formats (virtual vs. in-person)
Ability to adjust meeting times based on client availability
Knowledge of sending calendar invites via email
summary: Bennett Jones from Johnson and Johnson Insurance called Rick to schedule a meeting. After learning Rick's Wednesday schedule was unavailable, they agreed to a virtual meeting on December 11th at 4 PM. Bennett will send a calendar invite via email to confirm the arrangement.
